'''Elizabeth Mary Wright''' (1863-1958) was the wife of Tolkien's teacher [[Joseph Wright]], as well as a philologist and teacher in her own right.  Tolkien and the Wrights were close friends.<ref>[[J.R.R. Tolkien]]; [[Douglas A. Anderson]] (ed.), (2002) ''[[The Annotated Hobbit: Revised and Expanded Edition]]'', "[[Flies and Spiders]]", Note 14</ref>  [[Letter 6]] of [[J.R.R. Tolkien]]; [[Humphrey Carpenter]], [[Christopher Tolkien]] (eds.), ''[[The Letters of J.R.R. Tolkien]]'' was addressed to her.
